
INTRODUCTION

This project focuses on developing digital literacy skills required for students in today’s digital world. It covers online presence, communication, collaboration tools, and cybersecurity awareness.

TASK 1

I created an infographic using Canva to explain digital literacy concepts such as online safety and digital tools. The process was interesting as it involved visual design. The main challenge was selecting relevant content.

TASK 2

I created profiles on GitHub and LinkedIn. GitHub is used for showcasing projects, while LinkedIn helps in professional networking. I plan to use these platforms to build my portfolio over the next four years.

TASK 3

I used HackerRank to solve a beginner coding problem and created a Google Form quiz. These tools help improve problem-solving and collaboration skills.

TASK 4

I learned how to write professional emails and maintain proper communication. Poor communication can cause misunderstandings, which can be avoided by using correct tone and structure.

TASK 5

I studied phishing attacks and was surprised by how easily people get tricked. I will be more cautious while clicking links and sharing information online.

CONCLUSION

This project helped me understand essential digital skills and how to use online tools effectively and responsibly.
